{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859070406,"sessionID":"ses_2868f331effeKnZ7LxOY5SNSFk","part":{"id":"prt_d7972f55f001pG75yHkvhqo6S7","messageID":"msg_d79714803001tz37GAhZSPiW3S","sessionID":"ses_2868f331effeKnZ7LxOY5SNSFk","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-5b6e9e87bf424d72852e6cd9f4b63f33","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-014/design.md","content":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n实现 Valkey 存储后端，提供高性能的会话持久化能力，支持按过期时间和最后活跃时间索引以便垃圾回收。\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Application Layer                       │\n│                    (Session Manager, GC)                      │\n└────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘\n                                   │\n                                   v\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Store Interface                            │\n│  Ping / Get / Store / Update / Delete / List* / Close        │\n└────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘\n                                   │\n                   ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐\n                   │                               │\n                   v                               v\n┌──────────────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────────┐\n│      redisStore          │    │      valkeyStore         │\n│   (go-redis/v9 Client)   │    │   (valkey-go Client)     │\n└──────────────────────────┘    └──────────────────────────┘\n                   │                               │\n                   v                               v\n┌──────────────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────────┐\n│      Redis Server        │    │      Valkey Server       │\n│    (Single/Cluster)      │    │    (Single/Cluster)      │\n└──────────────────────────┘    └──────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Provider Selection\n\nSingleton `Storage()` reads `STORE_TYPE` env:\n- `redis` (default) → `redisStore`\n- `valkey` → `valkeyStore`\n- Other → init fails, provider remains nil\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### valkeyStore Struct\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### Key Constants\n\n```go\nconst (\n    defaultSessionPrefix        = \"session:\"\n    defaultExpiryIndexKey       = \"session:expiry\"\n    defaultLastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"\n)\n```\n\n### Key Design\n\n| Key Pattern | Type | Purpose | Score |\n|-------------|------|---------|-------|\n| `session:{id}` | String | JSON document storing SandboxInfo | - |\n| `session:expiry` | ZSET | Index by expiry timestamp | `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n| `session:last_activity` | ZSET | Index by last activity | `LastActivity.Unix()` |\n\n### valkeyClientOption\n\n```go\ntype valkeyClientOption struct {\n    InitAddress       []string\n    Password          string\n    DisableCache      bool\n    ForceSingleClient bool\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Constructor Functions\n\n#### `newValkeyStore(opts *valkeyClientOption) (Store, error)`\n\nCreates Valkey client via `valkey.NewClient()` with `ClientOption`:\n- `InitAddress`: from opts (comma-split addresses)\n- `Password`: from opts\n- `DisableCache`: from opts (optional)\n- `ForceSingleClient`: from opts (optional)\n\nReturns `&valkeyStore{cli: client, ...}`.\n\n#### `newValkeyStoreFromEnv() (Store, error)`\n\nEnvironment variables:\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated, split to `InitAddress` |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"` |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | `ParseBool`, sets `DisableCache` |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | `ParseBool`, sets `ForceSingleClient` |\n\n### Store Interface Methods\n\n#### Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n\n```go\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n    resp, err := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Ping().Build()).ToString()\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"store: ping failed: %w\", err)\n    }\n    if resp != \"PONG\" {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"store: unexpected ping response: %s\", resp)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n```go\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if sessionID == \"\" {\n        return nil, ErrEmptySessionID\n    }\n\n    key := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n    resp := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build())\n    if resp.Error() != nil {\n        if valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error()) {\n            return nil, ErrNotFound\n        }\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"store: get session %s: %w\", sessionID, resp.Error())\n    }\n\n    data, err := resp.AsBytes()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"store: read bytes: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n    if err := json.Unmarshal(data, &sandbox); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"store: unmarshal session %s: %w\", sessionID, err)\n    }\n\n    return &sandbox, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n\nValidates: non-nil sandbox, non-zero `ExpiresAt`, non-empty `SessionID`.\n\nUses `DoMulti` for atomicity:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    // ... validation ...\n\n    key := s.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n    data, _ := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n    \n    now := time.Now()\n    if sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero() {\n        sandbox.LastActivity = now\n    }\n\n    cmds := []valkey.Completed{\n        s.cli.B().Setnx().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Build(),\n        s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Score(float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())).Member(sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n        s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Score(float64(sandbox.LastActivity.Unix())).Member(sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n    }\n\n    resp, err := s.cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"store: multi exec: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    setnxOK, _ := resp[0].ToString()\n    if setnxOK != \"OK\" {\n        return ErrSessionExists\n    }\n\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n\nUpdates only the session JSON value, does NOT modify ZSETs.\n\n```go\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    // ... validation ...\n\n    key := s.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n\n    // Check existence first\n    exists := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build())\n    if exists.Error() != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"store: check exists: %w\", exists.Error())\n    }\n    count, _ := exists.AsInt64()\n    if count == 0 {\n        return ErrNotFound\n    }\n\n    data, _ := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n    \n    resp := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Build())\n    if resp.Error() != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"store: update sandbox: %w\", resp.Error())\n    }\n\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n\nAtomic cleanup of session key and both ZSETs:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n    if sessionID == \"\" {\n        return ErrEmptySessionID\n    }\n\n    key := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n\n    cmds := []valkey.Completed{\n        s.cli.B().Del().Key(key).Build(),\n        s.cli.B().Zrem().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n        s.cli.B().Zrem().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n    }\n\n    _, err := s.cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"store: delete sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n```go\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if limit <= 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    resp := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).\n        Min(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).\n        Limit(0, limit).Build())\n\n    if resp.Error() != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"store: list expired: %w\", resp.Error())\n    }\n\n    sessionIDs, _ := resp.AsStrSlice()\n    if len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    return s.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n}\n```\n\n#### ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\nSame pattern as `ListExpiredSandboxes` but uses `lastActivityIndexKey`.\n\n#### loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\nUses `Mget` for batch retrieval:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    keys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n    for i, id := range sessionIDs {\n        keys[i] = s.sessionKey(id)\n    }\n\n    resp := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build())\n    if resp.Error() != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"store: mget: %w\", resp.Error())\n    }\n\n    values, _ := resp.AsStrSlice()\n    var sandboxes []*types.SandboxInfo\n    \n    for i, v := range values {\n        if v == \"\" { // Missing key, skip\n            continue\n        }\n        var sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n        if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(v), &sandbox); err != nil {\n            continue // Skip unmarshal errors\n        }\n        sandboxes = append(sandboxes, &sandbox)\n    }\n\n    return sandboxes, nil\n}\n```\n\nNote: Comment states keys should be in same slot (cluster deployment consideration).\n\n#### UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n\n```go\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n    if sessionID == \"\" {\n        return ErrEmptySessionID\n    }\n\n    key := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n\n    exists := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build())\n    if exists.Error() != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"store: check exists: %w\", exists.Error())\n    }\n    count, _ := exists.AsInt64()\n    if count == 0 {\n        return ErrNotFound\n    }\n\n    if at.IsZero() {\n        at = time.Now()\n    }\n\n    resp := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).\n        Score(float64(at.Unix())).Member(sessionID).Build())\n    if resp.Error() != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"store: update last activity: %w\", resp.Error())\n    }\n\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Close() error\n\n```go\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) Close() error {\n    s.cli.Close()\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Helper Functions\n\n#### sessionKey(sessionID string) string\n\n```go\nfunc (s *valkeyStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n    return s.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Defined Errors (from store.go)\n\n| Error | Message | Trigger |\n|-------|---------|---------|\n| `ErrNotFound` | `store: not found` | Session key absent on GET, or missing on update activity |\n| `ErrNilSandbox` | `store: sandbox is nil` | Nil sandbox passed to Store/Update |\n| `ErrZeroExpiresAt` | `store: expiresAt is required` | Zero ExpiresAt on StoreSandbox |\n| `ErrEmptySessionID` | `store: sessionID is required` | Empty sessionID on any operation |\n| `ErrSessionExists` | `store: session already exists` | SETNX returns false (key exists) |\n| `ErrPasswordRequired` | `store: password is required` | Empty password when required |\n\n### Valkey-specific Error Detection\n\n```go\nif valkey.IsValkeyNil(err) {\n    return ErrNotFound\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\nFile: `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`\n\nTest categories mirroring Redis tests:\n\n| Test | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `TestValkeyStore_Ping` | PING → \"PONG\" |\n| `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_*` | Success, NotFound, EmptySessionID |\n| `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_*` | Success, NilSandbox, ZeroExpiresAt, EmptySessionID, Duplicate |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_*` | Success, NotFound, NilSandbox, EmptySessionID |\n| `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID_*` | Success, NotFound, EmptySessionID |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_*` | Success, Limit, ZeroLimit, NegativeLimit, SkipMissing, Empty |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_*` | Success, Limit, ZeroLimit |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_*` | Success, ZeroTime, NotFound, EmptySessionID |\n| `TestValkeyStore_Close` | Client close without error |\n| `TestValkeyStore_Mget` | Batch load with missing keys |\n| `TestNewValkeyStoreFromEnv_*` | Environment parsing validation |\n\n### Test Infrastructure\n\nUse `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` for local Valkey-compatible server:\n\n```go\nfunc setupTestValkeyStore(t *testing.T) *valkeyStore {\n    mr := miniredis.RunT(t)\n    cli, _ := valkey.NewClient(valkey.ClientOption{\n        InitAddress: []string{mr.Addr()},\n    })\n    return &valkeyStore{\n        cli:                  cli,\n        sessionPrefix:        defaultSessionPrefix,\n        expiryIndexKey:       defaultExpiryIndexKey,\n        lastActivityIndexKey: defaultLastActivityIndexKey,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\nVerify cluster mode compatibility:\n- Multi-address `InitAddress`\n- Key slot alignment for MGET\n- `ForceSingleClient` vs cluster auto-detection\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/store/\n  store.go              — Interface, errors, constants, singleton (existing)\n  store_redis.go        — Redis implementation (existing)\n  store_valkey.go       — Valkey implementation (new file)\n  store_test.go         — Redis + env tests (existing)\n  valkey_test.go        — Valkey-specific tests (new file)\n  doc.go                — Package doc (existing)\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | latest | Valkey client with builder API |\n| `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | latest | Test server |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | latest | Logging (init error) |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | local | SandboxInfo struct |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Valkey-go Builder Pattern\n\nUnlike go-redis's method chaining, valkey-go uses builder pattern:\n\n```go\n// Redis style\ns.cli.Get(ctx, key).Result()\n\n// Valkey style\ns.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build()).ToString()\n```\n\n### Multi-command Atomicity\n\n`DoMulti` executes multiple commands in a single request:\n\n```go\ncmds := []valkey.Completed{\n    s.cli.B().Setnx().Key(k).Value(v).Build(),\n    s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(z).Score(s).Member(m).Build(),\n}\nresp, err := s.cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)\n```\n\n### Response Handling\n\n```go\nresp := s.cli.Do(ctx, cmd)\n\n// Type conversions\nresp.ToString()      // string\nresp.AsBytes()       // []byte\nresp.AsInt64()       // int64\nresp.AsStrSlice()    // []string\n\n// Error check\nresp.Error()\nvalkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error())  // Nil sentinel\n```\n\n## References\n\n- AR-012 — Store interface (existing `store.go`)\n- AR-013 — Redis implementation (existing `store_redis.go`)\n- valkey-go: https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n- Session Store spec: `session-store/spec.md`"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/store/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":242,"character":20},"end":{"line":242,"character":39}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/deprecated"},"source":"deprecated","message":"s.cli.ZRangeByScore is deprecated: Use ZRangeArgs with ByScore option instead as of Redis 6.2.0.","tags":[2]},{"range":{"start":{"line":263,"character":20},"end":{"line":263,"character":39}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/deprecated"},"source":"deprecated","message":"s.cli.ZRangeByScore is deprecated: Use ZRangeArgs with ByScore option instead as of Redis 6.2.0.","tags":[2]},{"range":{"start":{"line":386,"character":20},"end":{"line":386,"character":44}},"severity":3,"code":"unusedparams","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedparams#unusedparams"},"source":"unusedparams","message":"unused parameter: opts"},{"range":{"start":{"line":398,"character":22},"end":{"line":398,"character":33}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/store/store_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":284,"character":5},"end":{"line":284,"character":24}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/gola